commit.message: Remove superfluous definitions from scanners.re.

re2c: Disable UTF-8

The regexes don't require UTF-8 features and work in ASCII mode as
well. Disabling UTF-8 reduces the size of the code generated by re2c by
a couple of KBs.

Makefile: Fix libFuzzer target

-DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Asan doesn't seem to work. Pass sanitizer flags
manually.

fuzz: Test more parser entry points

Use the upper bits of 'options' to select a parser mode from

- cmark_parse_document
- cmark_parse_file
- cmark_parser_new/feed/finish
- cmark_markdown_to_html

Rename `houdini_escape_html0` -> `houdini_escape_html`.

See #536.

houdini: Rework HTML entity table

The new layout saves about 20 KB and removes 50 KB of relocation
entries from the shared library, also speeding up loading.

Reduces the size of the shared library from 272 to 202 KB on Ubuntu
22.04.

utf8: Rework case folding

The generated switch statement compiled to around 85 KB of machine code
and rodata. Use a table and binary search instead, reducing the size of
the library from 345 to 272 KB on Ubuntu 22.04.

Replacement text is now preencoded as UTF-8.

This also removes the last Perl script from the repo.

Remove useless 'extern' keyword

Functions are extern by default.

'make debug' should build a shared library

The full test suite is only available to a shared library build.
Remove unused functions

ci: Test with ASan and rework CI matrix

Add CI tests with -fsanitize=address,undefined. This is a bit
complicated since our tests run through Python FFI and we have to

- link with -shared-libasan
- preload the ASan runtime
- disable LeakSanitizer because of false positives from Python

Use a single matrix on POSIX with four human readable labels:

    posix (os, compiler, build_type, sanitizers)

Disable gcc on macOS which is just an alias for clang.

Remove the valgrind leakcheck test. This should be covered now
by testing with LeakSanitizer on static builds, including tests
like spectest_executable. The full test suite is only available
to shared library builds which have to run without leak checks
for now.

Also rework the Windows matrix.
ci: Separate cflags from cc

ci: Make CMake matrix options work

CMAKE_OPTIONS had no effect, leading to the shared library not being
tested. Invoke cmake directly, so we don't have to deal with the mess
in Makefile.

test: Fix memory leaks in cmark.py

Free results of libcmark API function calls.
test: Fix memory leaks in api_test
CI: allow manual dispatch.

CI: use -gdwarf-4 with clang for compatibility with valgrind.

See #532.

Flag root node as open...

in `cmark_parser_new_with_mem_into_root`. Closes #532.

CI: do debug build so that assertions will run.

Closes #532.
Makefile: use ctest and `--output-on-failure` in `test` target.

Accept lowercase inline HTML declarations

Port of https://github.com/commonmark/commonmark.js/pull/284

test: simplify test execution environment handling

Use generator expressions to compute the new path and avoid
translations. This reduces complexity in the build and allows for a
different build layout.

Remove `source`, add `search` to list of block tags.

A spec 0.31 change we forgot in last release.
Spacing changes in changelog.txt.
Bump to 0.31.0, update changelog and man page
Update to 0.31.2 spec.txt.
Update test/spec.txt to commonmark 0.31.1 release.

build: provide some backwards compatibility for option changes

Introduce an author warning for the use of `CMARK_SHARED` and
`CMARK_STATIC` to redirect the author of the dependent package to
`BUILD_SHARED_LIBS`.

Avoid repeated `language-` in info string.

See commonmark/commonmark.js#277.
